{
  "texts": [
    "Firstly, the bidirectional nearest correspondence strategy is introduced to establish a reliable symmetric registration model.",
    "Secondly, aiming at the problem of partial overlap, a weighted pruning strategy is proposed to filter the wrong correspondence of points, and a probabilistic method is proposed to suppress the noise.",
    "A secondary network is introduced to predict the optimal annealing parameters, and a Hybrid distance generator network is used to learn the mixed distances of corresponding points, and a robust kernel function is used to estimate the corresponding confidence.",
    "Finally, a weighted optimizer is introduced into the network to solve the registration problem.",
    "In addition to the above network model of eliminating nonoverlapping regions, the researchers have proposed a series of methods to predict and supplement non-overlapping regions."
  ]
}